name: cyclohexane, 1,2,3-trimethyl-, (1.alpha.,2.beta.
Reason: The basic unit is cyclohexane, which has a melting point of 6.5°C. Each methyl group on the cyclohexane should slightly lower the melting point due to the introduction of bulk which can disrupt the crystal lattice making it less stable and more prone to melting at a lower temperature. Given that there are three methyl groups and considering the 1,2,3- arrangement providing some level of steric hindrance, an estimated decrease of about 10°C to 15°C per methyl group could be a rough approximation.
